<item>
            <title>[LU-1598] Bypass OI lookup in osd_fid_lookup() if it&apos;s for file creation</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-1598</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s unnecessary to call osd_oi_lookup() in osd_fid_lookup if it&apos;s a file creation because FID shouldn&apos;t never be re-used so we expect it to be not existed, which means we can bypass overhead of OI lookup at here, if it&apos;s really a duplicate FID from unexpected reasons, we should be able to detect it later while calling do_create-&amp;gt;osd_oi_insert().&lt;/p&gt;</description>
